<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT DRIVE AXLE WHEEL ENDS: FABCO SDA-12 - REASSEMBLY - LOWER KING PIN BRACKET</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LOWER KING PIN BRACKET</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Screw the lower kingpin ball stud into the lower kingpin until it just bottoms. Start the
                lower kingpin ball stud jam nut onto the stud.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The lower kingpin brackets with integral tie rod arms are handed. The left arm goes on the
                left steerable drive end and will position the tie rod to the rear when installed on the axle.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the proper bracket on the studs or bolts, whichever is used, projecting through the
                spindle yoke. Install the hardened washers and locknuts. Tighten to 175 ft-lbs. (235 N&#183;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
